cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO. 

The paper proposes a framework for transfer learning that leverages information obtained during training and can be computed on the fly at negligible cost. The framework is demonstrated on computer vision tasks and reinforcement learning environments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves neural networks and optimization, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics).
